  "title": "IT Support & Operations Lead – APAC & Australia",
  "description": "<p>The IT Support & Operations Lead is responsible for delivering first-level IT and network support, managing end-user and video conferencing services, and overseeing IT operations across the Asia-Pacific region and Australia. This role involves close coordination with offshore IT teams, leadership of regional IT resources, and ensuring consistent, high-quality IT service delivery across multiple geographies.<br /></p><p></p><p>IT Support & Service Delivery<br /><br />• Provide first-level IT and network support to office users<br />• Deliver end-user computing and video conferencing (VC) support<br />• Ensure timely incident resolution and service request fulfillment<br />• Maintain a high level of user satisfaction and service quality<br /><br /><br />Regional IT Operations Management<br /><br />• Oversee and manage IT operations across APAC (Singapore, Malaysia,Philippines)<br />• Coordinate and manage IT operations in Australia<br />• Ensure compliance with IT policies, standards, and service level agreements(SLAs<br />• Monitor system availability, performance, and operational stability</p><p><br />Team Leadership & Collaboration<br /><br />• Lead, mentor, and coordinate IT teams across Asia-Pacific locations<br />• Work closely with offshore IT teams to manage escalations and operational support<br />• Serve as the primary regional liaison between local offices and global IT functions<br /><br /><br />Stakeholder & Vendor Management<br /><br />• Engage with business stakeholders to understand IT needs and provideeffective solutions<br />• Coordinate with IT vendors and service providers to ensure service continuity<br />• Support IT asset management and operational planning activities<br /><br /><br /><strong>Skills and Competencies</strong></p><p>Strong expertise in <strong>first-level networking and desktop support</strong><br />Proven experience with <strong>video conferencing and collaboration platforms</strong><br />Demonstrated ability to manage <strong>regional IT operations</strong><br />Experience leading or coordinating <strong>distributed IT teams</strong><br />Excellent communication, leadership, and problem-solving skills<br />Experience supporting IT environments across <strong>APAC and Australia</strong><br />Familiarity with enterprise IT service management frameworks</p>",
